As pressure to capture the capital city of Ukraine, Kyiv, heightens, the Ukrainian government has armed volunteers at Kyiv with 18,000 machine guns and tasked them to defend the capital city, the British Broadcasting Corporation reports.
Among those who were provided with Machine guns to fight and defend their mother’s land, top football club players in Ukraine known as Dinamo Kyiv were seen posing in a photo with their full military kits ready for the battle.
It was stated that yesterday, these players were on their sports jerseys ready to play football for their nation, and today they are all in military kits ready to fight for their motherland.
ALSO READ: Social media reacts as Ukrainian female Soldier was killed while repelling Russian forces outside Kyiv
Below are some reactions of some individuals after seeing these post

Due to the critical situation their country is, authorities have called on the population to resist the invading troops all means, on hearing such order, these players have no choice instead of using their private jets to fly out of the country, they decided to take a brave step and join the civilians and fight the war.


